<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy" %>

<div class="zone--dark bg-db-bg min-h-screen pt-16">
  <%# ── Page Header ── %>
  <header class="border-b border-db-border">
    <div class="page-prose text-center">
      <p class="font-mono text-db-accent text-xs tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="text-db-text font-bold tracking-tight leading-tight
                 text-[clamp(2.4rem,5vw,4rem)]">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-xs tracking-widest mt-4">
        Last updated: April 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <%# ── Body ── %>
  <div class="page-prose">

    <div class="prose-db">

      <section class="mb-14">
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
          Death Bloom Coffee Roasters, LLC ("Death Bloom," "we," "us," or "our") is a specialty coffee roaster
          based in Denver, Colorado. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and share information
          about you when you visit our website at deathbloomcoffee.com, place an order, or subscribe to our
          newsletter. By using our site, you agree to the practices described here.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Information you provide directly</h3>
        <ul class="policy-list">
          <li><strong>Account information:</strong> name, email address, and password when you create an account.</li>
          <li><strong>Order information:</strong> shipping address, billing address, and payment details. Payment card data is processed by Stripe and never stored on our servers.</li>
          <li><strong>Newsletter subscription:</strong> email address when you opt in to our mailing list.</li>
          <li><strong>Communications:</strong> any messages you send us through the site or via email.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Information collected automatically</h3>
        <ul class="policy-list">
          <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> pages visited, referral URLs, browser type, operating system, and IP address.</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> session cookies required for the site to function (cart state, authentication) and analytics cookies if you consent. We do not use advertising or cross-site tracking cookies.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul class="policy-list">
          <li>To process and fulfill your orders, including shipping via EasyPost-integrated carriers.</li>
          <li>To send order confirmations, shipping notifications, and customer service replies.</li>
          <li>To send newsletter emails if you have subscribed — you can unsubscribe at any time via the link in any email.</li>
          <li>To improve our website, product offerings, and roasting program.</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations and protect against fraud.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide mt-4">
          We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">How We Share Your Information</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide mb-4">
          We share data only with service providers who help us operate our business:
        </p>
        <ul class="policy-list">
          <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing. Stripe's privacy policy governs their handling of your payment data.</li>
          <li><strong>EasyPost / shipping carriers</strong> — your name and shipping address are shared with the carrier to deliver your order.</li>
          <li><strong>Mailgun</strong> — transactional and newsletter email delivery.</li>
          <li><strong>Heroku / Salesforce</strong> — cloud hosting infrastructure for our application.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide mt-4">
          We may also disclose information when required by law, to enforce our Terms of Service, or to protect
          the rights and safety of Death Bloom and its customers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Cookies</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
          We use essential session cookies to keep you logged in and maintain your cart. If you opt in,
          we may set analytics cookies to understand how visitors use the site. You can disable cookies
          in your browser settings; doing so may affect site functionality such as cart persistence and
          account login.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
          We retain your account and order information for as long as your account is active or as needed
          to fulfill legal and business obligations (typically seven years for financial records). Newsletter
          subscribers are retained until you unsubscribe. You may request deletion of your account and
          associated data at any time by emailing us at the address below.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide mb-4">
          Depending on your location, you may have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="policy-list">
          <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
          <li>Correct inaccurate data.</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data.</li>
          <li>Opt out of marketing communications at any time.</li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (for EEA/UK residents).</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide mt-4">
          Colorado residents may have additional rights under the Colorado Privacy Act (CPA).
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <span class="text-db-text"><%= support_email %></span>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Security</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
          We use industry-standard security measures — HTTPS everywhere, encrypted passwords, and access
          controls — to protect your information. No method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure,
          and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
          Our site is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information
          from children. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such information, please contact us
          and we will delete it promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via
          email (if you have an account) or by posting a notice on the site. Continued use of the site
          after changes take effect constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-14">
        <h2 class="section-heading">Contact</h2>
        <p class="font-mono text-db-muted text-sm leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
          Death Bloom Coffee Roasters, LLC<br>
          Denver, Colorado<br>
          <span class="text-db-text"><%= support_email %></span>
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-12 border-t border-db-border flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-10">
      <%= link_to "← Back to Home", root_path,
            class: "font-mono text-db-muted text-xs tracking-widest uppercase hover:text-db-text transition-colors duration-150" %>
      <%= link_to "Terms of Service →", terms_of_service_path,
            class: "font-mono text-db-muted text-xs tracking-widest uppercase hover:text-db-text transition-colors duration-150" %>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
